[1] Americas
Date: Wed 12 Aug 2015
Source: PAHO [edited]
http://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&gid=31105+&Itemid=999999&lang=en


Cholera in the Americas - Situation summary
-----------
Since the beginning of 2015 up to epidemiological week (EW) 30 of 2015, a total of 20 388 cases have been recorded in 3 countries in the Region of the Americas: Haiti (20 043 cases), the Dominican Republic (344 cases) and Cuba (1 case). To date, no cholera cases have been reported in Mexico in 2015.

The last confirmed case of cholera in Cuba was reported in January 2015 by the Canada International Health Regulations (IHR) National Focal Point, indicating the case was an individual with history of travel to Cuba.

In the Dominican Republic, since the beginning of the epidemic (November 2010) to EW 28 of 2015, a total of 32 764 suspected cholera cases, including 489 deaths, were recorded. Between EW 1 and EW 28 of 2015, 344 suspected cholera cases were registered, including 11 deaths. This represents the double of the cases recorded for the same period in 2014. This situation in the Dominican Republic is linked to the cholera trends registered in Haiti during the same period.

In Haiti, since the beginning of the epidemic (October 2010) through 25 July 2015, there were 744 698 cholera cases, of which 426 884 were hospitalized (57 percent cumulative hospitalization rate), and 8826 deaths, with a national cumulative case fatality rate of 1.4 percent.
From January 2015 up to 25 Jul 2015 (EW 30), there were 20 043 cholera cases, including 15 921 hospitalizations (79 percent hospitalization rate), and 171 deaths (case fatality rate of 0.7 percent). In 2015, the number of cases and deaths recorded by epidemiological week show an increase in comparison to the corresponding week in 2014. In addition, in some weeks of 2015, the number of cases recorded is greater than what was recorded in 2012.

--
