[ProMED has noted 2 cases of cholera that were acquired in Cuba in travelers returning to Italy and the UK during 2015 (Public Health Agency of Canada: Travel Health Notice: Cholera in Cuba, Dominican Republic, Haiti and Mexico. Updated 20 Mar 2015; http://phac-aspc.gc.ca/tmp-pmv/notices-avis/notices-avis-eng.php?id=111; Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (24): Americas 20150703.3480336). These were not reported from Cuba to PAHO.

Additionally in Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (24): Americas: 20150703.3480336, a cholera case was reported in the Mexican state of Sonora, but it is unclear what is known about the Sonoran isolate regarding whether it is a O1 (or O139). Non-O1, non-O139 _V. cholerae_ does occur along the coasts of USA and Mexico, generally (but not always) causing milder illness without the epidemic potential - Mod.LL]

